really big for us.

00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:33.840
But the biggest
by far is probably

00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:35.840
the multiplayer and
the game services.

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:38.010
When we first released
"PBA Bowling Challenge",

00:05:38.010 --> 00:05:41.120
it didn't have the
multiplayer mode.

00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:44.210
We quickly started getting a
lot of fans, a lot of users.

00:05:44.210 --> 00:05:46.080
And it was really
tough to keep up

00:05:46.080 --> 00:05:48.830
with enough content
for all those users.

00:05:48.830 --> 00:05:51.390
They kept on coming back
asking for more alleys and more

00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:54.360
things unlocked,
more achievements.

00:05:54.360 --> 00:05:56.240
By adding multiplayer,
that really

00:05:56.240 --> 00:05:59.260
opened up to where people
would play forever.

00:05:59.260 --> 00:06:02.009
They could play random
people, their friends.

00:06:02.009 --> 00:06:03.550
And each game was
a little different.

00:06:03.550 --> 00:06:05.420
It was kind of funny,
having it be real time.

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:07.461
We were actually looking
for an asynchronous type

00:06:07.461 --> 00:06:08.460
of a multiplayer.

00:06:08.460 --> 00:06:10.020
And real time has
been fantastic,

00:06:10.020 --> 00:06:13.074
because it's actually exciting
to watch the other player

00:06:13.074 --> 00:06:14.740
roll through the
different bowling balls

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.910
